Creating a Constructor for a Laptop.
Write a Java program that:
	Defines a Laptop class with an attribute brand.
	The Laptop class should have a constructor that takes the laptop's brand as a parameter and initializes it.
	Use the Scanner class to take the laptop's brand as input from the user.
	The program should display the laptop's brand using a method in the Laptop class.
CODE:
package laptop;
import java.util.Scanner;
public class LAPTOP {
    String brand;
  //constructor
    public LAPTOP(String brand){
    this.brand = brand;
    }
    public void display() {
 System.out.println("Laptop brand: " + brand);
 }
   
    public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc =new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.println("Laptop brand is : ");
    String brand = sc.nextLine();
    
    }
    
}

 

***************TASK 01***********
 Write Your Name Using Nested Loops and Conditional Statements.
In this task, you’ll write a program that outputs your name using a combination of loops and conditional statements. You can use a 2D pattern (rows and columns) to simulate writing letters.
CODE:
package pattern;
public class Pattern {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
    int fp=20/2;
    int sp=20/2;
    for(int row=1;row<=10;row++)
    { 
        for(int col=1;col<=20;col++){
         if(col==fp || col==sp || row==10/2 && col>fp &&col<sp && col%2==0)
            System.out.print("*"); 
         else
             System.out.print(" "); 
        }
    System.out.println();
    fp--;
    sp++;
    }
    }
}

 

